<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="210" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,474,1327]" pageId="14" pageNumber="210">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,1194,1219]" pageId="14" pageNumber="210">Discussion.</emphasis>
Known from a single female from 
<taxonomicName box="[747,838,1194,1219]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ginungagapus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brasilia" status="sp. nov.">
<collectingCountry box="[747,838,1194,1219]" name="Brazil" pageId="14" pageNumber="210">Brasilia</collectingCountry>
</taxonomicName>
. Wing color pattern markedly similar to those of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Eutocus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ranesus" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="210">G. ranesus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[246,371,1230,1255]" pageId="14" pageNumber="210">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[427,525,1231,1254]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Lucida" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rogan" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[427,525,1231,1254]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="210">G. rogan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[532,658,1230,1255]" pageId="14" pageNumber="210">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
It is unlikely that 
<taxonomicName box="[867,985,1230,1255]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ginungagapus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brasilia" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[867,985,1230,1255]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="210">G. brasilia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[994,1081,1231,1254]" pageId="14" pageNumber="210" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is the actually the female of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Lucida" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rogan" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="210">G. rogan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[224,350,1266,1291]" pageId="14" pageNumber="210">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, given the distinct VHW pattern and wide distance between both distribution records.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
